  "prompt": "What do they ask in interviews of Junior Executive (Air Traffic Control), Airport Authority of India?",
  "response": "For Junior Executive (Air Traffic Control) interviews at the Airport Authority of India (AAI), the questions typically cover several key areas:\n\nTechnical Knowledge:\n1. Basic principles of Air Traffic Control\n2. Radar systems and communication technologies\n3. Aviation regulations and procedures\n4. Different types of airspace and their management\n5. Navigation systems and principles\n\nProfessional Skills:\n1. Communication skills\n2. Stress management abilities\n3. Decision-making under pressure\n4. Situational awareness\n5. Teamwork and coordination\n\nGeneral Topics:\n1. Knowledge of aviation industry\n2. Current trends in air traffic management\n3. Safety protocols\n4. International air traffic control standards\n\nPossible Interview Questions:\n1. Explain the role of an Air Traffic Controller\n2. How do you handle multiple aircraft simultaneously?\n3. Describe different types of aircraft separation\n4. What are the key responsibilities in air traffic control?\n5. How would you manage a potential mid-air collision risk?\n\nAdditional Assessment Areas:\n1. Physical and mental fitness\n2. English language proficiency\n3. Basic mathematical and analytical skills\n4. Psychological evaluation\n\nCandidates should prepare thoroughly in technical knowledge, communication skills, and demonstrate calm problem-solving abilities.",
